  "description": "The cyberops-v2 architecture provides a state-driven cybersecurity lab simulation where a central Simulation Orchestrator manages a global scenario store representing virtual machines, networks, and mission objectives. A Scenario Factory programmatically generates lab environments, which are then interacted with via a Terminal Interaction Engine that parses user commands and dispatches them to a modular Command Registry & Toolset. Executed tools update the shared simulation state, while a Virtualized Web Environment offers a synchronized browser UI for web-based exercises. All components share a common domain model ensuring consistent data structures across the system.",
